File: US President Donald Trump accused the WHO of failing in its duty to handle the coronavirus outbreak. JOHANNESBURG - The international relations department said it’s concerned about US President Donald Trump's decision to pull funding from the World Health Organization. Trump has accused the WHO of failing in its duty to handle the coronavirus outbreak. READ: Trump halts WHO funding, with world on edge over virus The South African government said it's alarmed as the decision comes amid the COVID-19 crisis. The total number of infections globally passed two million and over 130,000 deaths have been recorded. READ: Ramaphosa defends WHO after Trump virus lashing Government said it's hopeful Trump will reconsider and re-join the international fight against the pandemic. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.